<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-09-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.74/64</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-06"><hi rend="italic">September 6,
                                    1928</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received October 19.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 124</seg>
                            <lb/>
                            <seg rendition="#left">Diplomatic</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: For the information of the Department I
                            have the honor to state that on September 1, the Liberian Government
                            Radio Stations at Monrovia and Cape Palmas were opened for general
                            commercial radio traffic with the United States and all European
                            countries, jointly with the Radio Corporation of America. All Liberian
                            and United States Government business is to be handled at one-half the
                            regular rate.</p>
                        <p>Enclosed find copy of Departmental Notice No. 4–28, issued by the
                            Postmaster General and approved by the President, August 31, 1928.<note n="67" xml:id="d223fn67">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed>W. T. <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>